
Instructions for advanced human-machine interaction (attendance taking using deep learning: resnet-50)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: Download package

$ cd ~/Desktop

$ git clone https://github.com/Arijit1080/Face-Recognition-Based-Attendance-System

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 2: Download Trained Deep Learning Model

Download Models from link: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/12It2jeNQOxwStBxtagL1vvIJokoz-DL4?usp=sharing

Extract the zip, you will have a folder "data_dlib".

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 3: Create "data" and "data_faces_from_camera" folders

In the package, create a new folder named as "data".

Under the "data" folder, create a new folder named as "data_faces_from_camera".

Paste downloaded folder "data_dlib" under the newly created "data" folder

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 4: Execute commands to run
Once done with above setup, cd and run 

$ cd ~/Desktop/Face-Recognition-Based-Attendance-System

    (a) Collect the Faces Dataset:
    $ python3 get_faces_from_camera_tkinter.py
    
    (b) Extract the features:
    $ python3 features_extraction_to_csv.py
    
    (c) Take the attendance:
    $ python3 attendance_taker.py

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------




